3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Paradex implements hourly funding rate settlements on FLOKI/USDT perpetuals, calculating rates based on the premium/discount between perpetual and mark price. The platform's StarkNet architecture enables gas-efficient settlements while maintaining decentralized custody. Funding payments occur automatically at the top of each hour, with rates typically ranging from -0.5% to +2% daily during high volatility periods."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","FLOKI","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"FLOKI's meme token status creates substantial funding rate volatility on Paradex, often exceeding rates on major CEXs during trending periods. The pair's mid-tier volume provides sufficient liquidity for meaningful arbitrage positions while avoiding the extreme spreads of micro-cap tokens."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"FLOKI Funding Rate Historical Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"FLOKI/USDT funding rates on Paradex have shown distinct patterns correlating with broader meme token sentiment cycles. During bullish meme phases, funding rates frequently spike above 1% daily as retail traders heavily favor long positions. Conversely, during correction phases, funding often turns negative as leveraged longs get liquidated. The hourly settlement mechanism means rate changes can be more responsive than 8-hour settlement exchanges, creating short-term arbitrage windows. Historical data shows FLOKI funding volatility peaks during Dogecoin rallies and broader canine-themed token momentum."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"DEX Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Paradex's self-custodial nature creates unique arbitrage dynamics versus centralized exchanges trading FLOKI perpetuals. Rate differentials of 0.3-0.8% daily are common during high volatility periods, as DEX users often exhibit different positioning behavior than CEX traders. The platform's institutional-grade matching engine, built by former Jump Trading engineers, provides reliable execution for larger arbitrage positions. Cross-margining capabilities allow efficient capital utilization when running multi-pair funding strategies alongside FLOKI positions."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"StarkNet-Specific Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Trading FLOKI perpetuals on Paradex involves StarkNet-specific risks including potential network congestion during high activity periods and withdrawal complexities to Ethereum mainnet. The platform's early-stage status means limited historical data for backtesting funding strategies compared to established CEXs. Users must manage StarkNet gas tokens (STRK) for transactions and understand the platform's account abstraction model. Additionally, FLOKI's meme token volatility can cause rapid liquidations, making proper position sizing critical given Paradex's institutional-focused margin requirements."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often are FLOKI funding rates updated on Paradex?","answer":"FLOKI/USDT funding rates on Paradex are calculated and applied every hour at the top of the hour. This frequent settlement creates more responsive rate adjustments compared to 8-hour funding cycles on most centralized exchanges."},{"question":"What makes FLOKI funding rates different on a DEX versus centralized exchanges?","answer":"Paradex's self-custodial model attracts different trader behavior patterns, often resulting in more extreme funding rates during meme token rallies. The DEX structure also means no exchange can manipulate rates for profit maximization like some CEXs."},{"question":"Can I use portfolio margin for FLOKI positions on Paradex?","answer":"Yes, Paradex supports portfolio margining which allows cross-collateralization between FLOKI and other perpetual positions. This enables more capital-efficient funding rate arbitrage strategies compared to isolated margin requirements."},{"question":"What are the risks of funding rate arbitrage with FLOKI on StarkNet?","answer":"Key risks include StarkNet network congestion affecting trade execution, FLOKI's high volatility causing rapid liquidations, and the platform's early-stage development potentially having undiscovered bugs. Always maintain conservative position sizes and monitor network status."}]}]
